@NODE "Info" "What the hell is this?"

 These are Icons in the famous @{" MagicWB-Style " LINK "MagicWB"} and the new @{" «·» FWB-Style " SYSTEM "TTIGuide/Sound TTIGuide/Samples/Coolman.iff q"}.
 I use the same colours as spreaded with FantasticWB. Please read there on on how to use the correct colours.

 Anyway, I hope, you like these Icons or some of them. I think you don't need any further
 explanation, do you? ;) Only this: they are inspired by different sources. I hope nobody gets
 mad about that fact. Look at the @{" Credits " LINK "Credits"}, too.

 Please, don't use these Icons on any machine with @{" «·» Windoze " SYSTEM "TTIGuide/Sound TTIGuide/Samples/Win.8svx q"} installed or with an @{" «·» Intel processor " SYSTEM "TTIGuide/Sound TTIGuide/Samples/Booh.8svx q"}
 inside. They are made for use only on an @{" «·» AMIGA " SYSTEM "TTIGuide/Sound TTIGuide/Samples/NOTMAC.IFF q"}

 Just some words about the directory StarTrek: Yes, I am a @{" «·» Trekker " SYSTEM "TTIGuide/Sound TTIGuide/Samples/snd4.IFF q"} (How did you find out? ;-))
 I am using some of those Icons with the "Trekkie"-Database by Stefan Osterburg. A great
 program for all Trekkers out there.

 Before I forget: Some of the Trashcan-Icons are showing their secret only if you select them
 (it's just one mouseclick away...)

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Cardware" "This is CARDWARE!"

 @{" «·» TTIcons " SYSTEM "TTIGuide/Sound TTIGuide/Samples/BOGUS.IFF q"} are CARDWARE.
 Just take a look at these icons, TM-Brushes and pictures. If you like some of them,
 feel free to use them. But in that case, you'll have to send me a postcard.
 Should I make more Icons? Are you looking for anything special? Let me know.

 @{" Click here " LINK "Contact"} for My address.

@ENDNODE

